    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "My gut response is to agree with @sipa... but light wallets are also trust-based, so they should only be used in tandem with your own node anyway. I'm not sure doing their own address management makes sense, in that context.\r\n\r\nIn other words, the \"sane\" thing isn't doing their own address management *nor* relying solely on DNS seeds - it's peering with the user's own full node. And not sharing addresses with them is perfectly compatible with that.",
